==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -rid
<hw>-rid</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> +
<ets>saccharide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A simple sugar;
any of a number of sugars (including the trioses, tetroses, pentoses,
hexoses, etc.), not decomposable into simpler sugars by hydrolysis.
Specif., as used by some, a hexose. The monosaccharides are all
open-chain compounds containing hydroxyl groups and either an aldehyde
group or a ketone group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monosepalous</ent>⟦br⟧
